%I A396418 #8 May 29 2026 09:34:14
%S A396418 2,13,107,1423,13597,249533,2391041,77538289,119628479,1812918883,
%T A396418 14286143117
%N A396418 a(n) is the smallest n-digit prime that produces the most primes according to rules stipulated in Honaker's A048853.
%C A396418 In other words, the n-digit prime that has the most neighbors (per A048853), and in the case of a tie, the smallest such prime.
%H A396418 Michael S. Branicky, <a href="https://wp.technologyreview.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/MIT-Alumni-News-Puzzle-Corner-March-April-2026.pdf">Puzzle Corner: Problem M/A2. Most neighborly prime.</a>, MIT Technology Review, March/April 2026.
%F A396418 a(n) = min_{ arg max_{10^(d-1) <= p prime < 10^d} A048853(p) }.
%Y A396418 Cf. A048853, A050673, A396419.
%K A396418 nonn,base,more,new
%O A396418 1,1
%A A396418 _Michael S. Branicky_, May 26 2026
